<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="alone-adj">alone <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'ləʊn/    美 /ə'loʊn/  </p>
<p>[不用于名词前]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>单独的；独自的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Better be alone than in bad company. 
交损友不如无友。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s terrible to find oneself alone in such a place. 
发现独自一人在那样一个地方真可怕。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Believe me; you’re <strong>not alone in</strong> feeling sad.
相信我，并不只是你一个人感到难过。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>孤独的；寂寞的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The old man cried like a child because he <strong>felt so alone</strong>. 
老人感到很孤独，像小孩子一样哭了起来。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>仅仅；只：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In the United States alone, over 100 million cellphones are thrown away each year
仅在美国，每年就有超过1亿部手机被扔掉。</p><footer>2015 江苏</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="leave-let-sb-alone">leave / let sb alone</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不打扰某人；不管某人：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Why don’t you just mind your own business and leave me alone?
为什么你就不能少管闲事不打扰我？</p></div>

<h3 id="leave-let-sth-alone">leave / let sth alone</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不碰某物：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Leave the cakes alone. They’re for the guests.
别动那些蛋糕，那是给客人吃的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— I can’t remember those grammar rules!
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>. Practice more.  （2014 福建）<br />
A.You’re not alone<br />
B.It’s hard to say<br />
C.I’m afraid not<br />
D.It’s up to you  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. A  </p></div>